Judy Bernard, a systems specialist with the Chase Manhattan Bank, was married yesterday to Ronald Stephen Baron, a stockbroker with Herzfeld & Stern. The ceremony was performed at the Harmonie Club by Rabbi Sidney Schulman of Deal. N.J.

The bride, a graduate of the State University of New York at Buffalo, is a daughter of Mrs. Sylvia Bernard of Riverdale, the Bronx, and of Leon Bernard of Miami. Her father retired from the State Department of Agriculture.

Mr. Baron, son of Mr. and Mrs. Morton Baron of West Allenhurst, N.J., is an alumnus who Bucknell University. His father, who is retired, was an engineer with the Army.